      • alreadyGoodForFastExactInference

        public boolean alreadyGoodForFastExactInference()
        False if statistics indicates that the original graph does not need to be transformed to do efficient exact inference.

        True if addedEdges(),conditionedVariables(), mergedFactors(), factorsWithDuplicateVariables(), and variablesWithDuplicateEdges() are all zero.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(VariableEliminator.Stats other,
            VariableEliminator.Stats threshold)
        Returns -1/0/1 if these stats are deemed better than/same as/worse than other stats given specified threshold definition. Attributes for which threshold has a negative value will not be considered (other than that the threshold attributes are ignored). Attributes are compared in the following order:
        1. maxCliqueCardinality()
        2. addedEdgeWeight()
        3. maxCliqueSize()
        4. addedEdges()
        The first of these that are not equal will be used for the comparison.

      • meetsThreshold

        public boolean meetsThreshold(VariableEliminator.Stats threshold)
        True if these statistics satisfy the given threshold statistics.

        Specifically, compares the values of the following attributes:

        • addedEdges()
        • addedEdgeWeight()
        • maxCliqueSize()
        • maxCliqueCardinality()
        If for each these attribute of threshold that have a non-negative value, the current object has value that is less than or equal to the threshold value, then the threshold is satisfied.

      • conditionedVariables

        public int conditionedVariables()
        The number of variables that were eliminated by conditioning. That is, the number of variables with a fixed value when the variable eliminator is using conditioning.

        Note: this attribute is not used by compareTo(com.analog.lyric.dimple.model.transform.VariableEliminator.Stats, com.analog.lyric.dimple.model.transform.VariableEliminator.Stats) or meetsThreshold(com.analog.lyric.dimple.model.transform.VariableEliminator.Stats).

        See Also:
        Variable.hasFixedValue(), VariableEliminator.usesConditioning()

      • maxCliqueSize

        public int maxCliqueSize()
        Returns the size of the largest clique induced by the execution of the algorithm. The clique size is determined when a variable is eliminated and is equivalent to the number of non-eliminated neighbors of the variable plus one (for the variable itself).

      • maxCliqueSize

        public VariableEliminator.Stats maxCliqueSize(int size)
        Sets value of maxCliqueSize() and returns this object.

      • maxCliqueCardinality

        public long maxCliqueCardinality()
        Returns the cardinality of the largest clique induced by the execution of the algorithm. Like maxCliqueSize() but instead of the number of variables in the clique, this is based on the product of the cardinality of the variables in the clique.

      • maxCliqueCardinality
